		<div id="comment_body_64358712"><p>Limiting screen time doesn't really work all that well. If I limit my daughter's screen time on her tablet, she'll just switch over to her school's Chromebook and watch her favorite brain rotting YouTube Shorts content on that. I won't let her watch TikTok, but it doesn't matter because all of the popular content gets migrated over to the other video platforms anyway. Hell, most of them don't even bother removing the TikTok logos from it.</p><p>I have no control over the settings on her Chromebook (the school does<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
